OL,7,FProducts other than food continued to
OL,8,Fdeflate this month, with prices 0.8%
OL,9,Flower in May than the previous year,
OL,10,Faccording to the survey.
OL,12,FHelen Dickinson, chief executive of
OL,13,Fthe BRC, said: "In non-food, retailers
OL,14,Fcut furniture prices in an attempt to
OL,15,Frevive subdued consumer demand for big-
OL,16,Fticket items, and football fans have
OL,17,Fbeen able to grab some bargains on TVs
OL,18,Fand other audio-visual equipment ahead
OL,19,Fof this summer's Euros."
