OL,7,FFood prices continued to rise but at a
OL,8,Frate of 3.2% in May, down from 3.4% in
OL,9,FApril.
OL,11,FFresh food inflation fell to its
OL,12,Flowest level since November 2021,
OL,13,Fwhile ambient food inflation ` which
OL,14,Fmeans products that can be safely
OL,15,Fstored at room temperature, such as
OL,16,Ftinned goods, crisps, tea bags and
OL,17,Fbiscuits ` remained more stubborn.
